title: Alfonso Zvenyika Lambarda
text: Alfonso Zvenyika "Mosquito" Lambarda (born 25 November 1975 in <a href="Mbare%2C%20Harare">Mbare</a>) is a <a href="Demographics%20of%20Zimbabwe">Zimbabwean</a>/Australian <a href="professional">professional</a> <a href="flyweight">fly</a>/<a href="super%20flyweight">super fly</a>/<a href="bantamweight">bantam</a>/<a href="super%20bantamweight">super bantamweight</a> <a href="Boxing">boxer</a> of the 1990s and 2000s who won the Zimbabwe super flyweight title, African Zone 6 Flyweight Title, and <a href="List%20of%20Commonwealth%20Boxing%20Council%20Champions%23Light%20Flyweight">Commonwealth light flyweight title</a>, his professional fighting weight varied from , i.e. <a href="flyweight">flyweight</a> to , i.e. <a href="super%20bantamweight">super bantamweight</a>.
